Sastry 2005
: 28 (checklist) (as 

C. mammillifer

)

Actinal surface flat composed of two full series (
Fig. 6B
). Each plate rounded quadrate to irregularly polygonal in shape, surface convex, smooth and bare with no accessories other than either a single large, conical spine or tubercle present on nearly every plate. One or two irregularly shaped adjacent to inferomarginals. Actinal plates abutted, no fasciolar groove, each with coarse grained peripheral granules, 7 to 30 identical to those on other plates.
